tischer Intermedialitätsforschung, sondern bildet zudem eine wichtige Grundlage für eine noch zu schreibende Literaturgeschichte der Intermedialität.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aInterart studies. 4aIntermedialität. 4aKomparatistik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aIntermediality.  aearly modern period.  ainterart studies, comparative studies.1 aArend, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauer, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDröse, Astrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGess, Nicola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamm, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaak, Lothar van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMehltretter, Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Jürgen E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlotke, Seraina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobert, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobert, Jörg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aScheitler, Irmgard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmitz-Emans, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSinger, Rüdiger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStockhorst, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWerle, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabul